it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.tracker

Class ShapeTracker

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.objects.Semantics.Base
      • it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.tracker.ShapeTracker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Semantics.Logger, Tracker<MORPrimitive,SemanticItem>

    public class ShapeTracker
extends Semantics.Base
implements Tracker<MORPrimitive,SemanticItem>
    A Tracker implementation for MORPrimitive semantic objects and SemanticItem Item description.

    It implements a tracker that can track the shape of a semantic object, described as MORPrimitive into an SemanticItem item.

    Indeed, it is just a tracking set manger of Semantics.Primitive objects, semantically mapped in OWL through aMOR library (see: MORDescriptor). This class set the Tracker.Item unique identifier to be the OWL individual describing semantically the object, thus 'I' type parameters is replaced with OWLNamedIndividual.

    Most of the tracking implementations is available in the specific Tracker.Item description, this class is limited in managing the set of object an Tracker.UpdatingState. Nevertheless, it is also in charge to manage the clean() procedure for removing objects not perceived anymore if they are not update for a specific number of scans (see: setRemovingCntThreshold(int)).

      • update

        public Tracker.UpdatingState update(SemanticItem object)
        The basic implementation method for update an item in the tracking set.
        If the tracking set does not contains the new belief it calls add(MORPrimitive). Otherwise, for each elements in the tracked set it searches for the object with the same ID and calls Tracker.Item.update(Object).
        Specified by:
        update in interface Tracker<MORPrimitive,SemanticItem>
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the updating changes to the tracked set by considering the new given belief.

      • clean

        public java.util.Collection<Tracker.UpdatingState> clean()
        It search any Items in the tracking set that have a counter less than -1 * setRemovingCntThreshold(int). Since SemanticItem keep track of the times of scan than a current belief has been undated, if it goes less than 0 represents that the object is not seen anymore.
        Specified by:
        clean in interface Tracker<MORPrimitive,SemanticItem>
